                    You can edit your password through the <code>Zamdau</code>. There are 2 ways to resolve this issue depending on your login status:<br /><br />

                    <ol>
                        <li>I am logged into my <code>Zamdau</code> account</li>
                        <li>I'm not logged into my <code>Zamdau</code> account</li>
                    </ol>

                    
                    


                    1. I am logged into my <code>Zamdau</code>  account <br /><br />
                    If you can access your <code>Zamdau</code> account, you can edit your password by opening the <code>Zamdau</code> > go to the [Your name] tab in the top left corner of the screen > select Account Settings > select My Profile > select Password > select Edit > edit your password > complete verification via email sent to you.
                    class. This is the first item's accordion body.<br /><br />

                    2. I'm not logged into my <code>Zamdau</code> account<br /><br />
                    If you can't access your <code>Zamdau</code> account for reasons like losing your password, you can edit your password with these steps: Go to the Sign In > select <strong>Forgot password?</strong> > insert your email and check "I'm not robot" > in your email click on the link sent to you and alter you password > Submit.
                </div>
            </div>
