                <div class="accordion-body text-black">
                    The vast majority of scams are carried out by bad actors who try to impersonate  <code>Zamdau</code> employees and pretend to guarantee their own safety or try to gain some advantage through transactions on our platforms. <br /><br />

                    <h4>Detecting scams</h4> <br />
                    <p>Scams are usually identified by:</p>

                    <ol>
                        <li>Seller requests for off-platform payments.</li>
                        <li>Unofficial Shopee links that request sensitive account data, for example, two-step verification code (OTPs) or account passwords.</li>
                        <li>Spelling and grammar errors.</li>
                    </ol>
                    One of the most common ways used by bad people to obtain advantages is to inform you of any possible fluctuations on the platform related to your order or, even, to inform you that the shipping cost must be paid in another way, however, outside from the <code>Zamdau</code>  app.
